Program: Outlook
Title: Lone Telephone Box in California's Mojave Desert
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbqz0
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
'Possibly the most famous phone box in the world'. Godfrey Daniels and the story of the phonebooth in California's Mojave Desert whose number he called every day until someone answered. Also - the popularity of Miss World in India, homelessness in Moscow, Kozloduy, the Bulgarian nuclear reactor built in an earthquake zone and the story of outlaw Ned Kelly. Presenter: Heather Payton. Show less